comments: Caruso (CHI) absorbs the initial contact that occurs with Johnson (ATL) and takes a step backwards after the incidental contact.
Bey (ATL) legally contests DeRozan's (CHI) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Caruso (CHI) establishes a legal guarding position in Murray's (ATL) path and is dislodged from his position by Murray.
Young (ATL) reaches in and the contact with Dosunmu's (CHI) left arm is marginal.

As Caruso (CHI) secures the loose ball, he attempts to turn away from Young (ATL) and incidental head contact occurs.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Drummond (CHI) reaches for the rebound and marginal contact occurs with Capela's (ATL) arm.

Dosunmu (CHI) extends his left forearm into Young's (ATL) body and initiates contact that affects his SQBR.  Drummond (CHI) avoids initiating any illegal contact and the foul should have been assessed to Dosunmu.
Bey (ATL) commits a take foul on DeRozan (CHI).
Bogdanovic (ATL) slightly extends his hands towards White (CHI), but the contact is marginal.
Young (ATL) commits a take foul on Dosunmu (CHI).
Williams (CHI) avoids making any contact as he legally contests Bogdanovic's (ATL) jump shot attempt.
